text.0:
Ever wondered what false information looks like in other countries?

On this week's Full Fact Podcast, we spoke to fact checkers from Argentina and Nigeria to discuss their misinformation experiences, and to see what the UK could learn from them.

https://t.co/oDwlpuZkGm
text.1:
We’ve seen multiple sources claim that between 17,000-20,000 Royal Navy members died in the 1800s while trying to prevent the illegal slave trade.

While it is true that sailors died during these missions, it is very unlikely the death toll was this high
